DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       jjrreeff (JSON Reference) is a high-performance utility for creating,
       inspecting, searching, and manipulating condensed JSON project
       snapshots.  It operates as both a command-line tool and a programmatic
       TypeScript library.

       A snapshot is a single JSON file containing a directory tree, all file
       contents keyed by path, and optional AI instructions or project
       metadata.

       Snapshots are designed to be portable, streamable for large files, and
       AI-friendly with structured JSON I/O and an MCP server mode.  An
       interactive Terminal UI is also available for visual browsing.

       All commands accept stdin pipe input, e.g.: ccaatt ssnnaappsshhoott..jjssoonn || jjrreeff
       iinnssppeecctt ..

GGLLOOBBAALL OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       These flags apply to any command and must appear before the command
       name.

       ----jjssoonn, --jj
           Output structured JSON instead of human-readable text.  Every
           command supports this.

       ----ssiilleenntt, --ss
           Suppress all decorative output, progress indicators, and ASCII art.

       ----rraaww, --rr
           Raw output mode.  For the qquueerryy command this emits pure file
           content without headers or labels.

       ----jjqq, --qq _f_i_l_t_e_r
           Apply a jjqq filter to reshape or filter the snapshot state in memory
           before any core command receives it.  Uses jjqq--wwaassmm for portability
           across ARM and x86 devices.

       ----hheellpp, --hh
           Show global help listing all commands.  Append to any specific
           command for command-specific help: jjrreeff ppaacckk ----hheellpp ..

       ----vveerrssiioonn, --vv
           Print the version string jjrreeff vv11..11..00 ..  Use with ----jjssoonn to get
           {{\\version\":\\""11..11..00\\""}}"".

